──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
What this covers
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

bmcond (the busmatic-concentrator) is a userspace daemon that replaces
eQ-3's closed-source `multimacd` for HomeMatic radio modules.  Pure C,
links only against glibc.  No eQ-3 source code is incorporated.

Frame-codec logic (BidCoS, HmIP, DualCoPro, LLMAC) was written from
scratch based on:
- AskSinPP (GPL) — public AskSin-Frame-Layout reference
- piVCCU (GPLv2) — DualCoPro probe sequence cross-checked
- multimacd live-strace observation — protocol behaviour pattern

See CREDITS.md for full attribution.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Third-party material at runtime (not part of this repository)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

When deployed, bmcond talks to:
- eQ-3 closed-source binaries (rfd, HMServer.jar) via XML-RPC over PTY/HTTP
  — NOT linked, NOT redistributed by this repository.
- HomeMatic / HomeMatic IP radio hardware (HM-MOD-RPI-PCB, HmIP-RFUSB,
  HM-LGW-O-TW-W-EU) — protocol implementation here is for interoperability
  per §69e UrhG / EU-Directive 2009/24/EG Article 6.
